[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering JVM Behavior**\n\nI’m thinking about how the class field might be set during image build time by the native image. In the JVM, it's uncertain whether this holds true. Making a field null seems impossible without reflection, unless through a separate process. I could test by spawning a new Java process that runs a small main class to call setComprSize, with the static field initial null. But what about coverage? The dynamic-access agent might not instrument the child JVM without using a javaagent, which seems unlikely.\n\n**Considering static field access**\n\nI’m thinking about whether I could use `sun.misc.Unsafe` to set a static field. But based on my reasoning, it seems like that wouldn’t work. I might need to inspect the method style and check other tests to see if they use reflection for this. It's interesting how access methods can vary, and I'm curious about the best approach to take here!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e695fc3a1d3195e0169fc2942778c8197aa866703d29c5db2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_ClNT0HqWgteOPBpbweLF8XcAnGZ3gGF16_th7O6EzSuoPElpetyNz8EXMWzrFg01kYMdYOmrZjFIGxYWm6kWJ6-dESfh3UQnHyLhWtjZvxExThzzYphy6ZzAL0m6TlXLMdDz-xg3vMnvyP1jkSUGajqaUzMs1EoANZYDBnEzNkj8n2gKqg_7gmGNPlFwAkK8ZNTBw989BuqzXRDIQsw_DH7X8wh_Bpy88EiIUKJsg6eGjr2ltIWkCKg2ibx0jVITlZBASi8KdGiHa2EKpxNtVhx0X8tmPur3yoGDEqvvS7ozDqJ1A5HoM2dgEaJ5DR81TFIzzIkqW5TN3rO-X5Kdqx5fLHp98Dq1n6be5rrRk-xmjWxh7o_V14cYEEN7ordVILCol6GoLLhe-DBEXZIXb91pll12DT8MKrsfcRy-nQ6OUjKuWGd5XncOUeGeqYeHxrPxdvgs-0YaDldfA3luLmVufHoPVSvePFoyeWWS9moRgetwsiWzJg4bJubKSW7hViKWGobGO6cPx1KAGeFaKQc0bVzxylydhtxqq5oElxtZS4HcZpo_39tVe1rMm7YaERKLVz5JiOM5-i7B8yw53NUUSyHBEVBhGOpCkruDGLNu_RUt8OgVk6NJ-dBg-RZwWPmjhUYpduaXWrkUq7zG7ZSbCinPBK3N-LwooXm4FS-veru5_R7VxSZ0AK13vqJ9HUecq51WRR9CIqBazGAC9tdnYQIUki5BCb0q7I7y7H4HC8wif4YJWb23JhW-DgjpBm8UPDB9kANhKtl7glYDmEDjNLtW6uZF0gjxSHBLdnXCC4_vWRzA