ic field initial null. But what about coverage? The dynamic-access agent might not instrument the child JVM without using a javaagent, which seems unlikely.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering static field access**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether I could use `sun.misc.Unsafe` to set a static field. But based on my reasoning, it seems like that wouldn’t work. I might need to inspect the method style and check other tests to see if they use reflection for this. It's interesting how access methods can vary, and I'm curious about the best approach to take here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_v88cwe65izbKKa04YsCQHDNv|fc_0e695fc3a1d3195e0169fc294de4c88197a2cec58e001fb862", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -R \"getDeclared\\|setAccessible\\|Class.forName\\|MethodHandles\" -n tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1098, "output": 818, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22396, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778133313292, "responseId": "resp_0e695fc3a1d3195e0169fc2941c3bc8197be13c9eb697aab65"}}
